quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  3,122,"when two parties from among you were on the point of showing cowardice though Allah was their Guardian. And on Allah then, let the believers (put their) trust"
  3,123,"And Allah had helped you at Badr when you were weak, therefore fear Allah so as to be grateful (to Him)"
  3,124,"When you said to the believers, \"Is it not enough for you that your Fosterer should support you with three thousand of the angels, sent down"
  3,125,"Why not? If you are patient and on your guard and these (your enemies) come on you suddenly, your Fosterer will support you with five thousand of the angels, marked. will support you with five thousand of the angels, marked"
  3,126,"And Allah did not give this (assurance) except as a good news for you, so that your hearts should be at peace thereby, and there is no (other) help except that from Allah, the Mighty, the Wise"
  3,127,that He may cut off a portion from among those who did not believe or disgrace them so that they should go back (as) failures
  3,128,There is nothing for you in this affair whether He turns to them (mercifully) or punishes them because they are unjust
  3,129,"And whatever is in the skies and whatever is in the earth is Allah's. He protectively forgives whom He wills and He punishes whom He wills, and Allah is Protectively Forgiving, Merciful"
  3,130,"O you who believe ! do not swallow usury, multiplied many times and fear Allah that you may be successful"
  3,131,And guard (yourselves) against the fire which is prepared for the infidels
  3,132,"And obey Allah and the messenger, that you may be shown mercy"